Worst case time complexity (O(n² × k log k):
We are taking each element in the vector and comparing it with every other element by sorting both the strings. 
If both sorted strings are the same, they are grouped together. Once every possibility is checked, 
we simultaneously mark the corresponding indices as true in the visited array to make sure we do not create a new group with that element again. 
Once the group is formed, it is pushed into result. Finally, result is returned.


Optimal case Time complexity (O(n x logk):
We are using an unordered_map. For each element, we sort it and use the sorted string as the key. 
Strings that have the same sorted form are grouped together as values corresponding to that key. 
After processing all elements, we iterate over the map and push each value list into a new vector called result.

